latestPosts.caption:
Low carb meal. Paneer thecha recipe and moongdaal Chila. Recipe: 

For Moongdaal Chila - 
Soak your moongdaal for 40 mins. 
Grind it with 2 garlic cloves and 2 green chilies. 
Add Salt, turmeric and Coriander leaves 🍃 to the batter.
Cook it like a dosa and it’s ready :). 

Paneer Tetcha Sabzi: 

Slice the paneer. Coat it with salt and chili powder. 
Shallow fry the paneer. Paneer is ready. 

Thecha- Take 8-10 garlic cloves, 3 Green chili and handful of peanuts. Pound it or grind it. It’s ready. 

Sabzi- Take 1 tbsp of oil. 
Add cumin seeds and in onions. Cook it for 2 mins. 
Add in prepared thecha. 
Add salt, turmeric, red chili and kitchen king masala. 
Add in a little water if necessary(Spices should not burn) 
Add in 2-3Tbsp of curd. Mix it well. Add in prepared paneer. 
Cook it for 8-10 mins on low flame. Your low carb dish is ready.

latestPosts.caption:
Lasaniya bateka (Garlic potato- It’s a gujrati dish).

Recipe:

-Take small size potatoes and cook it. Remove the skin. 
-Take sufficient amount of oil that you can to coat all the potatoes, add in Cumin powder, chilli powder and Garam masala. Add it to the potatoes and coat the potatoes. 
-Take oil in the pan. Shallow fry the potatoes so that it doesn’t loose its shape when added to the gravy. 

Preparing Gravy:
Take 3-4 spoons of oil. Add in cumin and mustard seeds. Add in onion(I took 3 medium size onions)cook it well. Add in tomato purée. Cook it. Add in the garlic chutney. 

Preparation of garlic chutney: Soak dry red chili in water(6-7 chili). After it becomes softer take the chili add in 9-10 medium size garlic cloves and 1 teaspoon of cumin power). Blend it. 

-Add 2 tablespoon of garlic chutney after tomato is cooked. Let it cook for 5-7 mins. Add in the potatoes. Cook it for another 7-8 mins for the flavor to get absorbed by the potatoes. Turn off the flame and let the sabzi sit for 15-20 mins before serving to enhance the flavor of the potatoes in the gravy. Your food is ready to serve🤌✨.
